# Nature for Society

::: {.row .intro}
The landscape of Peru in 2060 has been optimised to maintain the provision of key ecosystem services for society [@gómez2023]. This is achieved through strong cross-sectoral planning and a sustainability transformation driven by the adoption of green technologies and the mainstreaming of the economic valorisation of ecosystem services and biodiversity.
:::

::: {.row .visual}
![](../img/scenario_images/society.jpg){style="border-radius: 8px;" fig-align="center" height="400"}
:::

------------------------------------------------------------------------

::: {.row .characteristics}
### Characteristics

<h4>[ <img src="../img/icons/climate_icon.png" alt="Climate Icon" style="width: 10%; max-width: 40px; vertical-align: middle; margin-right: 0.5em;"/> ]{.popover-key data-popover-key="climate"}[Climate Change]{.text-decoration-underline}:<strong> RCP 4.5</strong> </h4>

